Human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore, has asked the Nigerian Army to be loyal to the Nigerian people, rather than intimidating them. The army had pledged its commitment to the President of Nigeria and threatened to move with force on peaceful #EndSARS protesters in the country. Acting Director, Army Public Relations, Colonel Sagir Musa, in a statement on Wednesday night labelled the protesters as subversive elements and trouble makers. See Also






